    dc:description "Fig. 13 – Plangia geroi n. sp.: a, habitus of the male; b, habitus of the female; c, dorsal view of cerci and subgenital plate; d, stridulatory file under the left tegmen; e, stridulatory area on the left tegmen and mirror on the right tegmen; f, ventral view of the subgenital plate; g, ventral view of the subgenital plate and ovipositor; h, lateral view of the ovipositor." ;
